<task id="071" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.L2 — LOW-tier Api/* batch 2 (triage repair vs archive, ~22 files)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, low-tier, p23-l, bff-api, testing, triage</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-L</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Named Api/* test files (2nd quarter of ~88) are disjoint from sibling batches 070, 072, 073</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Triage and repair OR archive the LOW-tier Api/* tests — batch 2 of 4 (~22 files, 2nd quarter
    alphabetically). Per design.md §3.3 LOW-tier: per-file judgment — repair if unique
    response-shape contract; archive if duplicate of synthetic smoke.

    Per FR-20 P23.L START GATE: this batch MUST NOT start until P23.H AND P23.M are each ≥50%
    complete. Verify upstream progress before starting.

    For each test file:
    1. Determine: KEEP (repair) or ARCHIVE (rename per §6.5)
    2. If KEEP: repair assertions; apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`; verify Pass
    3. If ARCHIVE: rename to `&lt;OldName&gt;.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`; add `archive-ledger.md` entry

    ESCALATION TRIGGER: If archive count in this batch exceeds 10 files → ESCALATE per NFR-04
    BEFORE proceeding. File `escalations/archive-approval-T-071.md`.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY repaired
    file's diff would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-071-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). NO silent deletion (NFR-06). Per §6.2 every touched test
    ends in `repaired`, `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. `Failed` is
    FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist with API endpoint + smoke-test judgment.</role>

  <goal>
    ~22 Api/* test files (2nd quarter) triaged. Repaired files Pass. Archived files renamed +
    ledgered. Zero Failed.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="archive-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Archive count &gt;10 in this batch triggers owner escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">MUST NOT silently delete tests; archive via rename</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state (or archived)</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-19">All LOW-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-20">Start gate: P23.H and P23.M each ≥50% complete</constraint>
    <constraint source="batch-partition">Batch 2 covers 2nd quarter of Api/* files alphabetically; respect partition</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Second quarter of the LOW-tier Api/* batch. Same triage discipline as batch 1 (task 070).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="040" status="not-started">≥50% of P23.H required</dependency>
      <dependency task="050" status="not-started">≥50% of P23.M required</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/&lt;second quarter of files alphabetically&gt;</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify FR-20 start gate: ≥50% of P23.H + ≥50% of P23.M complete. If not, HALT.</step>
    <step order="2">List `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/*.cs`. Sort alphabetically. Take 2nd quarter (~22 files) → batch 2.</step>
    <step order="3">From Phase 0 baseline TRX, identify failing tests within batch.</step>
    <step order="4">For each file: REPAIR vs ARCHIVE judgment per §6.2 + design.md §3.3.</step>
    <step order="5">Track archive count. If approaching 10 → file `escalations/archive-approval-T-071.md` per NFR-04 BEFORE proceeding past 10.</step>
    <step order="6">For REPAIR: edit; if &gt;50% replacement → §4.8 escalate. Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`.</step>
    <step order="7">For ARCHIVE: rename to `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`; add `archive-ledger.md` entry with justification.</step>
    <step order="8">After each file: verify outcome via `dotnet test --filter`.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` with disposition table.</step>
    <step order="10">Verify `git status` shows NO production changes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test</tool>
    <tool name="git">status + mv (for archive rename)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">~22 Api/* test files (repaired or archived)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md (entries for archived files)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All batch-2 LOW-tier tests Pass, Skip-with-reason, or are archived; zero Failed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-20 start gate verified</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file repair diff &lt;50% (NFR-02); archives renamed per §6.5</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Archive count ≤10, OR `escalations/archive-approval-T-071.md` exists with owner approval (NFR-04)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has §6.2 final end-state trait OR is archived</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No overlap with batches 070, 072, 073 files</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <scope-extension date="2026-05-31">
      Wave 1 baseline reconciliation (task 008) confirmed Api/Office/* cluster: 10 failures
      in OfficeEndpointsTests (50% rate). Falls within existing relevant-files glob (2nd
      quarter alphabetically — O range) — annotation only.
      See `notes/handoffs/phase23-scope-delta-2026-05-31.md`.
    </scope-extension>
  </notes>
</task>
